wikipedia_page.main: Thomas Daley (15 November 1933 – 23 January 2020) was a professional footballer born in Grimsby, Lincolnshire, who played as a goalkeeper in the Football League for Grimsby Town and  Huddersfield Town. He later played for Peterborough United, Gainsborough Trinity and Boston United in non-league football.
